Class XmlSectionModel

java.lang.Object
  org.cast.cwm.xml.XmlSectionModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, org.apache.wicket.IClusterable, org.apache.wicket.model.IDetachable, org.apache.wicket.model.IModel<XmlSection>, ICacheableModel<XmlSection>
public class XmlSectionModel
extends Object
implements org.apache.wicket.model.IModel<XmlSection>, ICacheableModel<XmlSection>

A Model pointing to an XmlSection. Must be used since XmlSection is not serializable, but XmlSection and DtbookDocument objects are generated once and cached so the models can detach and re-attach efficiently. This method implements equals() and hashCode() based on the document name and xml ID. Since these are generally stable and uniquely identify a piece of XML content, this model can be used as a cache key.

getKey

public Serializable getKey()
Description copied from interface: ICacheableModel
Return a hash key for this model's object. This is similar to hashCode() (and can even fall back on hashCode()), but must be done explicitly. This is because some implementations of hashCode() (e.g. HibernateObjectModel) rely on the existence of a datastore object. Changes to the underlying datastore can change the hashCode or throw a NullPointerException.
